org.apache.flink.runtime.execution.librarycache

类 BlobLibraryCacheManager.LibraryCacheEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.execution.librarycache.BlobLibraryCacheManager.LibraryCacheEntry
  • 封闭类:
    BlobLibraryCacheManager

    private static class BlobLibraryCacheManager.LibraryCacheEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    An entry in the per-job library cache. Tracks which execution attempts still reference the libraries. Once none reference it any more, the class loaders can be cleaned up.

      • classLoader

        private final java.net.URLClassLoader classLoader

      • referenceHolders

      • libraries

        private final java.util.Set<PermanentBlobKey> libraries
        Set of BLOB keys used for a previous job/task registration.

        The purpose of this is to make sure, future registrations do not differ in content as this is a contract of the BlobLibraryCacheManager.

      • classPaths

        private final java.util.Set<java.lang.String> classPaths
        Set of class path URLs used for a previous job/task registration.

        The purpose of this is to make sure, future registrations do not differ in content as this is a contract of the BlobLibraryCacheManager.

    • 构造器详细资料

      • LibraryCacheEntry

        LibraryCacheEntry(java.util.Collection<PermanentBlobKey> requiredLibraries,
                  java.util.Collection<java.net.URL> requiredClasspaths,
                  java.net.URL[] libraryURLs,
                  ExecutionAttemptID initialReference,
                  FlinkUserCodeClassLoaders.ResolveOrder classLoaderResolveOrder,
                  java.lang.String[] alwaysParentFirstPatterns)
        Creates a cache entry for a flink class loader with the given libraryURLs.
        参数:
        requiredLibraries - BLOB keys required by the class loader (stored for ensuring consistency among different job/task registrations)
        requiredClasspaths - class paths required by the class loader (stored for ensuring consistency among different job/task registrations)
        libraryURLs - complete list of URLs to use for the class loader (includes references to the requiredLibraries and requiredClasspaths)
        initialReference - reference holder ID
        classLoaderResolveOrder - Whether to resolve classes first in the child ClassLoader or parent ClassLoader
        alwaysParentFirstPatterns - A list of patterns for classes that should always be resolved from the parent ClassLoader (if possible).
